tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The blood count shows mildly elevated erythrocytes and MCHC, and a markedly increased platelet distribution width, while all other parameters are within normal limits. These findings may reflect individual variation or mild hemoconcentration; no evidence of anemia, infection, or thrombocytopenia. Clinical correlation is recommended if symptoms are present.
